		"body": "### Summary\r\nFixes the **Link to Note** command not working when triggered via keyboard shortcut or command palette.\r\n\r\n### Problem\r\nThe **Link to Note** command did nothing when accessed through:\r\n- Keyboard shortcut (`Alt+Shift+L`)\r\n- Command palette (`Ctrl+Shift+P`)\r\n\r\nThe command only worked when invoked from the Tools menu.\r\n\r\n### Root cause\r\nThe command’s `enabledCondition` was too restrictive and disabled execution when triggered from modal contexts such as the command palette.\r\n\r\n### Fix\r\nUpdated the `enabledCondition` in  \r\n`packages/app-desktop/gui/WindowCommandsAndDialogs/commands/linkToNote.ts`  \r\nto allow execution when `gotoAnything` is visible, while still requiring:\r\n- a selected note\r\n- an active editor (Markdown or Rich Text)\r\n\r\nThis follows the same pattern used by other editor commands in the desktop codebase.\r\n\r\n### Manual testing\r\n- `Alt+Shift+L` opens **Link to Note**\r\n- `Ctrl+Shift+P` → **Link to Note** works\r\n- Tools menu behavior unchanged\r\n- Command remains blocked in non-editor modals (e.g. Settings)\r\n\r\nFixes #13029\r\n",
